## 2. System Architecture

### 2.1 Architecture Overview

The indexer module is a single TypeScript file (src/indexer.ts) that exports one public function runIndexer(). Internally it delegates to three private functions: detectAvailableIndexer(), buildCommand(), and executeIndexer(). The module depends on VS Code APIs and Node.js built-ins only.

Architecture Diagram

Architecture Diagram

### 2.2 Component Diagram

Component Diagram

Component Diagram

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Component | Responsibility | Technology |
| extension.ts | Command registration, calls runIndexer() | VS Code Extension API |
| indexer.ts | Runtime detection, command building, execution | Node.js child\_process |
| config.ts | Static configuration (INDEXER\_SCRIPTS, labels) | TypeScript constants |
| VS Code Settings | Stores preferredIndexer value | VS Code Configuration API |
| Output Channel | Displays indexer output to user | VS Code Output Channel API |

### 2.3 Deployment Architecture

This is a VS Code extension — deployed as a .vsix package installed in the user’s VS Code instance. No server-side deployment.

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Environment | Description |
| Development | npm run watch → TypeScript compiled to out/ → F5 launches Extension Development Host |
| Production | vsce package → .vsix file → installed via VS Code marketplace or manual install |

### 2.4 Communication Patterns

|  |  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| From | To | Protocol | Pattern | Description |
| extension.ts | indexer.ts | Function call | Sync (async/await) | handleRunIndex() calls runIndexer() |
| indexer.ts | VS Code Config | API call | Sync | getConfiguration().get() |
| indexer.ts | OS Shell | child\_process.exec | Async (callback) | Spawns probe/indexer processes |
| indexer.ts | Output Channel | API call | Sync | channel.appendLine() |
| indexer.ts | VS Code Window | API call | Async | showInformationMessage() / showErrorMessage() |

## 3. API Design

**Note:** This is an internal module API (TypeScript functions), not a REST API.

### 3.1 API Overview

|  |  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| # | Function | Visibility | Description | Source |
| 1 | runIndexer(workspaceRoot) | Public (exported) | Entry point — orchestrates full flow | UC-01, UC-02, UC-03 |
| 2 | detectAvailableIndexer() | Private | Probes runtimes in priority order | UC-01 |
| 3 | buildCommand(key, workspaceRoot) | Private | Constructs shell command | UC-02 |
| 4 | executeIndexer(command, cwd, key) | Private | Spawns process, streams output | UC-03 |
| 5 | commandExists(cmd) | Private | Checks if command is available | UC-01 (helper) |
| 6 | isWindows() | Private | Platform detection utility | UC-02 (helper) |

### 3.2 Function: runIndexer

**Implements:** UC-01, UC-02, UC-03, UC-04

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Attribute | Value |
| Signature | async function runIndexer(workspaceRoot: string): Promise<boolean> |
| Exported | Yes |
| Called by | extension.ts → handleRunIndex() |

**Parameters:**

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
| workspaceRoot | string | Yes | Absolute path to workspace root directory |

**Return Value:**

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Type | Description |
| Promise<boolean> | true if indexer ran successfully, false otherwise |

**Algorithm:**

export async function runIndexer(workspaceRoot: string): Promise<boolean> {
 // 1. Read preferred indexer setting
 const preferred = vscode.workspace
 .getConfiguration("kiroSdlc")
 .get<string>("preferredIndexer", "auto");

 // 2. Determine indexer key
 const indexerKey = preferred === "auto"
 ? await detectAvailableIndexer()
 : preferred as IndexerKey;

 // 3. Handle no runtime found
 if (!indexerKey) {
 vscode.window.showWarningMessage(
 "No compatible runtime found. Install Python, Java, or Node.js."
 );
 return false;
 }

 // 4. Build command
 const command = buildCommand(indexerKey, workspaceRoot);
 if (!command) { return false; }

 // 5. Execute
 return await executeIndexer(command, workspaceRoot, indexerKey);
}

### 3.3 Function: detectAvailableIndexer

**Implements:** UC-01

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Attribute | Value |
| Signature | async function detectAvailableIndexer(): Promise<IndexerKey \| null> |
| Exported | No (private) |

**Algorithm:**

async function detectAvailableIndexer(): Promise<IndexerKey | null> {
 const priority: IndexerKey[] = ["python", "java", "nodejs", "powershell", "bash"];
 for (const key of priority) {
 const script = INDEXER\_SCRIPTS[key];
 const checkCmd = "check" in script ? script.check : null;
 if (checkCmd && await commandExists(checkCmd)) {
 return key;
 }
 }
 // Platform fallback
 return isWindows() ? "powershell" : "bash";
}

**Error Handling:**

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Condition | Behavior |
| Probe times out (> 5s) | commandExists resolves false, moves to next |
| Probe throws error | commandExists resolves false, moves to next |
| All probes fail | Returns platform default (never returns null in practice) |

### 3.4 Function: buildCommand

**Implements:** UC-02

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Attribute | Value |
| Signature | function buildCommand(key: IndexerKey, workspaceRoot: string): string \| null |
| Exported | No (private) |

**Algorithm:**

function buildCommand(key: IndexerKey, workspaceRoot: string): string | null {
 switch (key) {
 case "python":
 return `python ${path.join(workspaceRoot, ".analysis/code-intelligence/scripts/python/main.py")} "${workspaceRoot}"`;
 case "java":
 if (isWindows()) {
 return `"${path.join(workspaceRoot, ".analysis\\code-intelligence\\scripts\\java\\run.bat")}" "${workspaceRoot}"`;
 }
 return `bash "${path.join(workspaceRoot, ".analysis/code-intelligence/scripts/java/run.sh")}" "${workspaceRoot}"`;
 case "nodejs":
 const nodeDir = path.join(workspaceRoot, ".analysis/code-intelligence/scripts/nodejs");
 return `cd "${nodeDir}" && npm install && npx tsx src/full-indexer.ts "${workspaceRoot}"`;
 case "powershell":
 const psScript = path.join(workspaceRoot, ".analysis\\code-intelligence\\scripts\\powershell\\full-indexer.ps1");
 return `powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File "${psScript}" -RootDir "${workspaceRoot}"`;
 case "bash":
 const bashScript = path.join(workspaceRoot, ".analysis/code-intelligence/scripts/bash/full-indexer.sh");
 return `bash "${bashScript}" "${workspaceRoot}"`;
 default:
 return null;
 }
}

**Platform Handling:**

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Platform | Path Separator | Shell | Notes |
| Windows | \ | cmd.exe (via exec) | Uses .bat for Java, backslash paths |
| Linux/Mac | / | /bin/sh (via exec) | Uses bash for Java, forward slash paths |

### 3.5 Function: executeIndexer

**Implements:** UC-03

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Attribute | Value |
| Signature | async function executeIndexer(command: string, cwd: string, key: IndexerKey): Promise<boolean> |
| Exported | No (private) |

**Algorithm:**

async function executeIndexer(command: string, cwd: string, key: IndexerKey): Promise<boolean> {
 return new Promise((resolve) => {
 const channel = vscode.window.createOutputChannel("Kiro Code Indexer");
 channel.show();
 channel.appendLine(`[Kiro] Running ${INDEXER\_SCRIPTS[key].label} indexer...`);
 channel.appendLine(`[Kiro] Command: ${command}`);
 channel.appendLine("");

 cp.exec(command, { cwd, timeout: 120000 }, (err, stdout, stderr) => {
 if (stdout) { channel.appendLine(stdout); }
 if (stderr) { channel.appendLine(stderr); }
 if (err) {
 channel.appendLine(`[Kiro] ERROR: ${err.message}`);
 vscode.window.showErrorMessage(`Indexer failed: ${err.message}`);
 resolve(false);
 } else {
 channel.appendLine("[Kiro] ✅ Indexing complete!");
 vscode.window.showInformationMessage("Code indexing complete!");
 resolve(true);
 }
 });
 });
}

**Timeout Behavior:**

When timeout: 120000 is exceeded, Node.js exec kills the child process and calls the callback with an error whose killed property is true and signal is SIGTERM.

### 3.6 Function: commandExists

**Implements:** Helper for UC-01

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Attribute | Value |
| Signature | function commandExists(cmd: string): Promise<boolean> |
| Exported | No (private) |

**Algorithm:**

function commandExists(cmd: string): Promise<boolean> {
 return new Promise((resolve) => {
 cp.exec(cmd, { timeout: 5000 }, (err) => resolve(!err));
 });
}

### 3.7 Function: isWindows

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Attribute | Value |
| Signature | function isWindows(): boolean |
| Exported | No (private) |

function isWindows(): boolean {
 return process.platform === "win32";
}

## 4. Database Design

Not applicable — this feature has no database. All data is in-memory (configuration) or file-system (scripts).

## 5. Class / Module Design

### 5.1 Package Structure

kiro-sdlc-agents/src/
├── extension.ts ← Entry point, command registration
├── indexer.ts ← Runtime detection + execution (THIS FEATURE)
├── config.ts ← INDEXER\_SCRIPTS, INDEXER\_OPTIONS constants
├── injector.ts ← File copy logic (KSA-3)
└── checksum.ts ← File integrity verification (KSA-11)

### 5.2 Type Definitions

// In config.ts
export const INDEXER\_SCRIPTS = {
 python: { check: "python --version", label: "Python" },
 java: { check: "java --version", label: "Java" },
 nodejs: { check: "node --version", label: "Node.js" },
 powershell: { check: "powershell -Command \"$PSVersionTable.PSVersion\"", label: "PowerShell" },
 bash: { check: "bash --version", label: "Bash" }
};

// Derived type
type IndexerKey = keyof typeof INDEXER\_SCRIPTS;
// = "python" | "java" | "nodejs" | "powershell" | "bash"

### 5.3 Design Patterns

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Pattern | Where Used | Rationale |
| Strategy | buildCommand() switch | Each runtime has different command construction strategy |
| Chain of Responsibility | detectAvailableIndexer() loop | Probes are tried in order until one succeeds |
| Promise wrapping | executeIndexer(), commandExists() | Wraps callback-based cp.exec in async/await |
| Null Object | buildCommand() returns null | Signals invalid key without throwing |

### 5.4 Error Handling

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Error Condition | Function | Behavior | User Impact |
| No runtime detected | detectAvailableIndexer | Returns platform default | Transparent fallback |
| Platform default unavailable | runIndexer | Shows warning toast | User sees “No compatible runtime” |
| Invalid IndexerKey | buildCommand | Returns null | runIndexer returns false silently |
| Process fails (exit ≠ 0) | executeIndexer | Shows error in channel + toast | User sees error details |
| Process timeout (> 120s) | executeIndexer | Process killed, error shown | User sees timeout message |
| Probe timeout (> 5s) | commandExists | Resolves false | Transparent, moves to next |

