## 7. Security Design

### 7.1 Command Injection Prevention

Commands are constructed from: 1. Static templates (hardcoded in buildCommand()) 2. workspaceRoot — from vscode.workspace.workspaceFolders[0].uri.fsPath (trusted VS Code API) 3. No user-supplied arbitrary strings in commands

**Risk Assessment:** Low — no untrusted input enters command construction.

### 7.2 Execution Policy

* PowerShell: -ExecutionPolicy Bypass is scoped to the single script invocation
* This does NOT change the system-wide execution policy
* The script being executed is one the user explicitly injected into their workspace

### 7.3 Process Permissions

* Child process inherits the VS Code process permissions (user-level)
* No privilege escalation
* No network access required by the indexer

## 8. Performance & Scalability

### 8.1 Performance Targets

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Operation | Target | Measurement |
| Runtime detection (all probes) | < 10s worst case | 5 probes × 5s timeout |
| Runtime detection (typical) | < 2s | First probe succeeds |
| Indexer execution | < 120s | Timeout kills at 120s |
| Command building | < 1ms | Synchronous string operations |

### 8.2 Resource Usage

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Resource | Usage | Limit |
| Child processes | 1 at a time (sequential probes, then 1 indexer) | Max 1 concurrent |
| Memory | Minimal (stdout/stderr buffered by exec) | Default exec buffer (1MB) |
| CPU | Delegated to child process | User’s machine resources |
| Disk I/O | Indexer reads source files | Workspace size dependent |

## 9. Monitoring & Observability

### 9.1 Logging

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Log Event | Level | Fields | Destination |
| Indexer started | INFO | runtime label, command | Output Channel |
| Indexer output | INFO | stdout/stderr lines | Output Channel |
| Indexer success | INFO | completion message | Output Channel + Toast |
| Indexer error | ERROR | error message | Output Channel + Toast |
| No runtime found | WARN | warning message | Toast |

### 9.2 Output Channel Format

[Kiro] Running Python indexer...
[Kiro] Command: python /path/to/.analysis/code-intelligence/scripts/python/main.py "/workspace"

... indexer output lines ...

[Kiro] ✅ Indexing complete!

Or on error:

[Kiro] Running Python indexer...
[Kiro] Command: python /path/to/script.py "/workspace"

... partial output ...
... stderr output ...

[Kiro] ERROR: Command failed with exit code 1

