| 3 | package.json | Verify | kiroSdlc.preferredIndexer configuration — already exists |
| 4 | src/extension.ts | Verify | handleRunIndex() calls runIndexer() — already exists |

### Implementation Notes

1. **Current code already implements this feature** — src/indexer.ts contains the full implementation matching this TDD
2. The existing code uses cp.exec with callback pattern (not streaming) — stdout/stderr are appended after process completes, not in real-time
3. **Potential improvement:** Use cp.spawn for real-time streaming (future enhancement, not in scope for KSA-5)
4. The commandExists function uses the check command directly (e.g., python --version) which may produce output — this is acceptable as the output is discarded

### Acceptance Verification

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| # | Criterion | How to Verify |
| 1 | Detect Python | Install Python, set preferredIndexer=auto, run indexer → should detect Python |
| 2 | Detect Java | Uninstall Python, install Java, run indexer → should detect Java |
| 3 | Preferred override | Set preferredIndexer=nodejs, run indexer → should use Node.js directly |
| 4 | Output Channel | Run indexer → “Kiro Code Indexer” channel appears with output |
| 5 | Success toast | Indexer completes → “Code indexing complete!” toast appears |
| 6 | Error handling | Remove all runtimes → warning message appears |
| 7 | Timeout | Create script that sleeps 130s → process killed after 120s |

## 12. Appendix

### Glossary

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Term | Definition |
| IndexerKey | TypeScript type: "python" \| "java" \| "nodejs" \| "powershell" \| "bash" |
| Probe | A lightweight command (e.g., python --version) to check runtime availability |
| Output Channel | VS Code read-only text panel for displaying process output |
| exec | Node.js child\_process.exec() — spawns shell, buffers output, calls callback |
| spawn | Node.js child\_process.spawn() — spawns process, streams output (not used here) |

### Open Questions

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| # | Question | Status | Answer |
| 1 | Should we use spawn for real-time streaming? | Resolved | No — exec is simpler and sufficient for this use case. Real-time streaming is a future enhancement. |
| 2 | Should python3 be tried as fallback on Linux? | Open | Currently only tries python. Could add python3 fallback in future. |
| 3 | Should timeout be configurable? | Resolved | No — hardcoded 120s is sufficient. Can be made configurable in future if needed. |

